				</span>
									<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=3696'>			
	
		</a><br>

				<span class=text_smallest>
								</span>

								
			
			
									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 7913 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_3.gif' border=0 alt='6 ratings - 3.1 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>1.&nbsp; Resist system is a problem at high levels.&nbsp; Just as one example, we had a bard running around a bunch of players near the zone-in of HoH, training mobs on players (training is a very large problem too btw), and we had a full raid up front trying to get to one of the trials in HoH, we got the bard mez'd, and kept him mez'd, but were trying to snare him (because as soon as anyone hit him, he was gonna zone out, rebuff, and come right back in to train some more), and we tried for probably 5-7 minutes, while he was mez'd, and never got it to stick, with 4-5 druids, and 4-5 rangers chain casting snare.&nbsp; You know what, thats fine that snare shouldnt stick alot in PvP, its a strong PvP spell, but for it to NEVER land. . .&nbsp; Its the same with alot of spells with little or no resist modifiers.&nbsp;&nbsp; You may as well not cast them in PvP, save your mana.&nbsp;&nbsp; Maybe give some AA abilities that give your spells resist modifiers. (example, 5 aa's to reduce all your spell modifiers by -20, and ability to purchase 10 levels of this aa ability (for top resist modifier to all spells of -200)--And if eq resists get even higher due to future expansions, you just add in more aa's so more can be purchased to get higher resist modifiers if it appears resists are getting out of whack again).&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2.&nbsp; PvP rewards.&nbsp; YES they are needed.&nbsp; Some sort of PvP content for people to get excited about.&nbsp; IDEALLY, some kind of PvP content that encourages mass PvP.&nbsp; I'd suggest "borrowing" ideas from other games and work them into the EQ PvP environment.&nbsp; My ideal (since you ask) would be&nbsp;a zone (or maybe 3-4 zones) where you have mass PvP battles to "win" by taking over a castle, or something of that nature.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>Ideally, it would start with 3-4 castle zones, with a boss mob in the castle.&nbsp; The first guild that can kill the boss mob takes over the castle for the week, and their reward is access to an instanced raid zone with really nice loot/exp that only the winner each week can access.&nbsp; (as EQ's expansions evolve, and loot becomes better and better, the loot/mobs in this reward zone should also be increased, so it keeps interest in taking the zone).&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>Once they take over the castle, they can name one ally guild to defend castle and participate in raid zone.&nbsp; The following week, the winner and their ally guild must defend the castle at a SET TIME, (say 3 hours starting at a particular time), against ALL COMERS, so in other words, those two guilds against the entire server.&nbsp; To defeat defenders, attackers must destroy some NPC type object, that has 200k hps, but doesnt fight back, located deep in the castle, behind NPC doors with 100k hps that you have to destroy to get into.&nbsp;&nbsp; During set 3 hour siege time, ALL NPC's other than doors and final target, are despawned, to avoid training, using NPC's in PvP, etc.&nbsp; If defenders keep you from killing the 200k NPC target for the 3hour set time, they win, and continue with access.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;If the defenders lose, then the guild that does the most damage to them wins access for the next week, and can choose their own ally (but ally cant be one of the previous defenders from immediate prior week, and defenders cant join winners guild during following week either--to avoid setups).&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>This could be something added just to PvP servers.&nbsp; It would make good PvP content, that would add some excitement to EQ's PvP game.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I know, my idea might be a little ambitious, but PvP "content" that encourages mass PvP (not just 1 on 1&nbsp;PvP)&nbsp;in some way, would be AWESOME.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3.&nbsp; Safe zones are fine, for places such as the bazaar.&nbsp; How else are you gonna make use of those utilities, you cant have afk traders if you can pk them.&nbsp; If you DO take away some of the other safe zones, then you need to DEAL with bard and enchanter faction songs at the same time, because they WILL use those songs to get the NPC's in those current zones to kill anyone they attack.&nbsp; In other words, nobody but bards and chanters will go into those zones very often (Twilight, Nexus).&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4.&nbsp; SHADOW KNIGHTS.&nbsp; You took charm and fear out of the PvP game because it was too unbalancing.&nbsp; You set a precedent there.&nbsp; Use that precedent to take out Shadow Knight Harmtouch in PvP.&nbsp; Its far too unbalancing in PvP, because there is no cast-time.&nbsp; You see, with wizard manaburn, and necro lifeburn, there is a fairly long cast time.&nbsp; You can see it start, it gives you time to try to gate to escape, or to heal yourself above 75%, or to RUN.&nbsp; But with Harmtouch, there is no cast time, so once you hit 75%, you are instantly dead.&nbsp;&nbsp; There is just no fighting SK's because you gave them spells that are almost irresistable, and a horse than you cant outrun (so if they cant hit you with a spell, then they will chase you down and slash on your back until you hit 75%, and then hit the HT button).&nbsp; Its just real stupid to try to fight a SK for anyone anymore.&nbsp; You gotta do something about that. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5.&nbsp; TRAINING.&nbsp; I know, its illegal on all servers other than SZ, so why deal with only one server's problem.&nbsp; You are wrong.&nbsp; It happens on all PvP servers (as well as PvE servers).&nbsp; Make it where if a mob travels more than 100 feet, it will only keep agro on the person that agrod it.&nbsp; Also, make mobs that summon, summon regardless of whether damage has been done to them, that way, a bard cant run by with its AOE spells that dont do damage, agroing mobs, and pulling a train clear across a zone without fear of being summoned, because he did no damage.&nbsp;&nbsp; Its kinda dumb how a ranger/druid can keep agro on a mob with snare snare snare (or some other debuff) and build more agro than you could with doing damage, yet the mob wont summon unless damage is done by someone.&nbsp; </DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
