			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Oh, I left one thing out that is really a big annoyance in PvP.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>6.&nbsp; Zoning and gaining HPs.&nbsp; When you are near death, down below 2 bubs of health left, if you zone, you will come out on the other side of the zone with GAINED health.&nbsp; You gain to the amount of HP items you have on.&nbsp; So, for instance, if I am down to 500 hps, and I have 2000 hps worth of gear on, and I zone, my hps automatically jump back up to 2000 hps.&nbsp; Its an automatic 1500 hp heal, just for zoning.&nbsp; It makes people who are fast zoners almost impossible to kill.&nbsp; Its a bug you should fix, and it affects PvP because certain people use this bug to "heal" themselves over and over and over again by constantly fighting at zonelines, so you can never really kill them.&nbsp; People who are good at this bug, use it solo to take out full 6 person groups (or force full groups to leave)&nbsp;who dont have near the hp gear as they do, but are the same level.&nbsp; </DIV>
																		
