			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1)Pvp immune zones, nice to have a few of them.&nbsp; Maybe turn knowledge into a pvp zone.&nbsp; To prevent people from book hugging, altho as a wizard i never really had a problem with it, but other classes who can't kill as fast probably have.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2)Bard mana drain.&nbsp; With EP+ instruments it can drain near 700 or more mana per hit.&nbsp; That is a LOT.&nbsp; Especially when its recast is 18 seconds.&nbsp;&nbsp; Halv the mana it drains.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3) harm touch needs to go.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4) make training RAIDS illegal on sullon.&nbsp; Sure at first it was nice on paper, till people who were obsessed with it came into play.&nbsp; Now raids are trained EVERY SINGLE night.&nbsp; It just makes people quit the server.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5)Manaburn/lifeburn really aren't that much of a threat. Imo they can stay, but if removed no biggie as well.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>6)Resists.&nbsp; Like i said before, make 10% chance for full resist at 100 to the resist, up to 50% chance for full resist with 500.&nbsp; -the resist check from the spell.&nbsp; For example, lure (-300) would be like casting vs 200 to the resist making it 20% chance to resist with 500 resist.&nbsp; Its kinda silly for someone with 500 to say resist fire be immune to mage/druid nukes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>7) lessen rezzbox timer to 45 seconds or so, to prevent with rezzbox training.&nbsp; Since even if you make training raids illegal, people will still do it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>8) rewards for insignias.&nbsp; Maybe items such as, 50 charge sow potions, ldon points, 1 charge reviviscence items, exp gains, maybe class specific items.&nbsp; Or even instead of insignias, institute a pvp point system.&nbsp; And make it so being in a group/raid divides the points that a person would give.&nbsp; And use that for rewards instead.&nbsp; That would also solve the problem that some classes like clerics, cannot kill very well at all.&nbsp; It would allow them to go out and pvp and still achieve points by being grouped with say a wizards who excells in pvp.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>9) Far fetched one, but close time on pvp servers.&nbsp; Its ridiculous how much that gear overpowers people in pvp.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>9) Tone down selos a bit.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>10) Tone up AM3 a little bit, right now it is completely worthless in pvp.&nbsp; It was nerfed TOO hard.&nbsp;&nbsp; I agree it was overpowered pre-nerf getting hit for almost 1K a pop non trueshot, but it got nerfed too hard.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>11) Keep stuns/root/snare same resistwise as it is now.&nbsp; So where 200ish mr makes it very hard to snare/root.&nbsp; That works.&nbsp; Those spells can deeply hinder pure melees.&nbsp; After it was nerfed from 100 to 200 it made me quit my monk, because i had troubles with bazaar gear just getting 120 mr.&nbsp;&nbsp; Some might say get pumice stones, but then unless you have your buffs up perfectly, you have to click them all off to dispel the snare that lands on you (hoping no one is on you cause you cant channel).&nbsp;&nbsp; And since snare/root/stun is literally no mana cost, it should stay so its heavily resisted.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>12) As much as i would hate it being a wizard <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> , make all pets very high immune to snare/root.&nbsp; Mages need help with pvp, people can disable their pets so easily.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>13) Shamans need help with resists with their spells.&nbsp; They are very easy to resist.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>14) Bard Divine aura.&nbsp; Raise refresh time on it to 10 min, put it up with every other da in the game.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Just a few ideas to try and help balance classes.&nbsp; This mainly is focused towards sullon zek, since it is the only pvp server i have ever played on.</DIV>
