												1. Resists need to be fixed, theres enough info on that<br><br>2. Class balance. How do you expect a warrior to have an honest shot at killing, say, a bard who can run at 160% runspeed (or whatever) and cast spells without even stopping and with no mana cost? SKs Harmtouch, rangers trueshot+EQ=AM3, bards in general, and manaburn are all Pains for other classes to counter.<br><br>3. Lures are annoying. certain spells like lure and lifetaps almost always land, while fire and magic based spells (read- most mage stuff) will bounce off you at  99% rate as long as you're in decent gear<br><br>3. Vallon zek/RZ/TZ. Players are outright AFRAID to pvp. its all crossteaming, and you're lucky to see more than 2 pk based guilds. What happens to those guilds? They get ostracized by the 90% of "anti-pk" players.<br><br>4. Training. high end pvp involves player A training guild B with mobs.<br><br>5. RZ- all items are no drop since LDoN augs, effectivly making the loot code useless. only low level players lose items in pvp now.<br><br>6. SZ- The "territory war" server is trivial now that anyone can use PoP or nexus scions to appear at a whim wherever they wish. Remember back before luclin when sneaking a good character into the evil areas like OT and LOIO was basically a death sentence? And Nuetrals defended misty thicket while goods protected their areas? (all 3 of them!) I know that 5 expansions adds a TON of new zones, enough for everyone not to step on each others toes...but thats the problem.<br><br>I honestly think the only way to fix pvp is to make a classic+kunark (maybe velious) only server, and tweak the classes from there.
