						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>I'll keep mine short so I know it will be read.&nbsp; PVP can never be "Fixed" but there are a few easy things that could be done that would improve it greatly.</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Instakills:&nbsp; </STRONG>Manaburn, Lifeburn, Improved Harmtouch.&nbsp; Add a 4-5 second cast timer to Improved Harmtouch to bring it in line with the other two spells, or just remove all three spells from pvp.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Training:&nbsp; </STRONG>Impossible to moderate since&nbsp;pvp servers&nbsp;do not&nbsp;have enough GMs and they actually need to witness it which never happens let's face it.&nbsp; There have been a few GREAT suggestions to impede trainers however without the need for GMs.&nbsp; Ressurection boxes on PVP servers should only last 10 seconds.&nbsp; Alternatively, make a 5 second delay that wipes all their buffs and stuns them when they click accept.&nbsp; After 5 seconds passes, they zone.&nbsp; Another easy fix:&nbsp; Kill selos in all raid zones.&nbsp; Another option, mobs that summon when damaged should summon every 15 seconds when agroed, and then normally when they are damaged.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Resists:&nbsp; </STRONG>Druids and other non resist adjust nukers are really hurting.&nbsp; Return&nbsp;the druid&nbsp;dot line to the nearly unresistable state it used to be in.&nbsp; A nice idea/quick fix would be to simply lower the max a persons PVP resists can be to 350 or 400.&nbsp; This will lessen the huge gear advantage some people have.&nbsp; Root and snare should hardly ever land between 150 and the max resist level, however it shouldn't be impossible.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Zone bug:&nbsp;&nbsp;</STRONG>This one must be so easy to fix.&nbsp; When you zone, you should remain at the level of HP you zoned with.&nbsp; Not shoot back up to 40%, which is a hell of alot of hitpoints for a melee class.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>PVP Reward: </STRONG>Insignias should be worth something.&nbsp; A cool idea would&nbsp;be every month or so an automated script counts all the insignias in every persons bank.&nbsp; It then deletes them and assigns a reward based upon the amount of insignias.&nbsp; Oh, a&nbsp;person should only be able to obtain&nbsp;2 insignias per person per day&nbsp;to avoid abuse of the system.&nbsp;Give insignias to the other pvp servers and implement the same exp loss&nbsp;on death as SZ.&nbsp; You might aswell, since LDON augments have made all items no drop and therefore there is no risk to pvping on Rallos Zek.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Bard manadrain: </STRONG>Nerf it so that a bard can never drain faster than an enchanter of equal level.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-Hamadryad Ouch</DIV>
<DIV>Sullon Zek</DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
																		
