			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<P>Whats wrong with PVP--- alot, but it still "ok" if u adapt&nbsp; and its the only reason why i still play the game since it came out 1999 - if changes are to drastic and not well tested&nbsp; - it will prop break the current balance - more than acutally helping.</P>
<P>Whining about Instant kill spell/aa ??? - neither MB/LB nor Harmtouch are instant kill spells with there 66% dmg spell dmg/ 75% max hp is definitly -and despite all "whining" - try to "hunt" down a skilled&nbsp;horsing ghosting well aa and time geared cleric/druid&nbsp; and get him to 74%&nbsp;&nbsp;... its not that easy...I also wonder who the hell acutally is using/advertising the use of Spear DD for SK - I never ever have successfully landed a "SK-spear spell in pvp except maybe on&nbsp; ungeared not yet lvl65 players - which i dont bother to "fight" anyhow- and so i stopped using them&nbsp;for pvp along time ago&nbsp;- the only spell that does land on is our Lifetap and if your lucky the lifedrain dot and if they are fully debuffed/dispell even darkness might stick....but then if the traget is snared it will die from dead&nbsp;via melee dmg and its no point using a HT if you can hit for triple hit 652dmg.</P>
<P>Try to harmtouch any well geared 9k+ warrior/Knight who is still above 50-60% of their max HP and they laugh at your &nbsp;- my best pvp ht&nbsp;was a 5900dmg (66% of 9k+ HT)&nbsp;on a 11-12k hp warrior at approx.&nbsp;50% of his life and he almost lived though it - beside there 1s casting time&nbsp; 4 charges rechargable Invul - Items for usable for all classes - get them use them and survive any HT/MB/LB... and laugh.</P>
<P>If spell resist are "change" even slightly it propably will have "bigger" impact then most of you will expect to the better or the worse...only thoughout testing would help... btw the new necro dots seem to stick rather well even with 300++ mr/fr</P>
<P>I stopped playing my lvl60 enchanter for pvp in 2000 as single (all landed at that time) shammy/nerco &nbsp;dot not cure/dispelled meant certain death and nothing but Rapture and ManaDrain&amp;Dispell would work/stick in pvp ---&nbsp;and switched to a Wizard - that atleast was able to nuke those dotting classes down before the dot would have killed him ...and enjoyed doing 14k+ manaburn hits every 2h&nbsp;;-) but i agree the current 75% max hp limit is better...and i still &nbsp;bought MB back after refund-&nbsp;but even than prenerfed Ranger could kill the wizard before the manaburn casting time was done(&lt;5s) - Thanks Thurgen for demonstrating this serveral times to Yoggi. Before AA come out i level up a rogue - but I couldnt stand the "running" - so i retired him at lvl59 once SoL and AA skill came and sticked to the Wizard.</P>
<P>In 2002 with&nbsp;the new high of resist gear and only Lures sticking and the highend&nbsp;"melee" weapons&nbsp; - i switched Main char again I finally found my prefered class which i currently keep playing.</P>
<P>... and if classbalance/PvP get nerfed get out of hand... I already found an alternativ to play...</P>
<P>We were promised and ask for many "changes" since 5years -eg Bards for the Dark team on VZ...but most never happened - so the top Dark guilds adapted and went 4 team to hold vs the Light 3 team guild</P>
<P>-&gt;it now&nbsp;guild vs guilds on vallon zek - the "best change that could actually happen would be to "remove" the team aspect on VZ and allow like on RZ that no racial restrictions are giving.</P>
<P>Splorge 65SK&nbsp; &amp;Marem 65Enc &amp;&nbsp;Yoggi 65 Wiz &amp; Marez&nbsp;59 Rogue&nbsp;&nbsp;www.ancient-dawn.de&nbsp; Vallon Zek </P>
