												<P>Pvp /city holding &nbsp;rewards would be nice - i recommend to check eqguildwars for some further "ideas" how pvp server for eq &amp;eq2 can/should be.</P>
<P>Two way&nbsp;zones like Sebilis/chardok with seperated entrance/exit as well as multiple entrance / exist&nbsp; would avoid the sometimes annoying zone camping/zone dancing.... </P>
<P>And "invul" into non save zones from places like nexus as in guildwars does help as well - if its a one way portal... </P>
<P>Changing radically the &nbsp;resist checks on 14min snares/2 min roots or &nbsp;250dmg/sec stacked&nbsp;dmg time&nbsp; spells will also destroy pvp more than do well.</P>
<P>Currently Shammy/Rogue (without tendonslicer)/Magicans might need some "pvp" improvements for there pvp dmg dealing abilitlies - possible improve the Debuff mod&nbsp;for pvp&nbsp;on Malo/Mala/Tash lines so the spells stick better once the target is debuffed&nbsp;.</P>
<P>In my experience the&nbsp;GoD Nerco dots seem to work out alot better in pvp.</P>
<P>Instant Evac/gates/zoning &nbsp;with /heal/ effect semi annoying...but no biggie.</P>
																		
