		<tr>
			
			<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>

						
							
				
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=23719' class="auth_text" style="font-weight:bold;">WeatheredSZ</a>
				<br>

								
				<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
									Newbie
								<br>
									Posts: 4<br>
													Registered: 04-09-2004
				
				</span>
									<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=23719'>			
	
		</a><br>

				<span class=text_smallest>
								</span>

								
			
			
									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 7691 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_3.gif' border=0 alt='2 ratings - 3.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>resists are a problem for none lure casters. i do agree that they should be limited in pvp, without killing them for pve though, since they're still required for some encounters. also, if you lower reists, you must lower the damage output done by player spells, it only makes sense. fights should last a little longer than 2 lucky nuke crits.</DIV>
<DIV>here's a suggestion. if it's possible, make it so that when a player is attacked by another player, he enteres "pvp mode":</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-the player's resists are lowered&nbsp;- this could also mean your resists are lowered towards mobs aswell, making attacks on raids more suspensful and maybe even ruling out the need to train... must be tested of course</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-run speed could be modified, leaving class given advantages, but balancing them somewhat (bards - love you guys, but very high end bards are just crazy, also horses are known to make ppl cuss in ooc, heh)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-consider making bard songs on players use mana (again, sorry for you lowbie bards, it's extremely hard for you to get a kill, but high end...)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-damage spells&nbsp;do less damage (though this could be done outside of pvp mode, similar to the current 66% restriction)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-i don't know if lowering a player's hp to a "class standard" is a smart idea, since eq is ALSO about gear and players should have something to show for their efforts, even in pvp... but "very high end" geared players (especially casters) have an hp ressource that somewhat defies the built in class disadvantages in relation to their benefits. i still think this is worth giving some time to think about though, considering this is about "balancing" eq pvp</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-consider giving (forcing) "lure" based spells a chance to do only do&nbsp;partial damage on every cast, regardless of resists, making a fight less predictable.&nbsp;also consider giving raptures a chance to break before the time is up, and also give stuns a chance to land more often (turns a fight around), all in proportion of course</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-here's a fun thing i've had to battle with so many times: a necro can lifetap a lvl 1 mob and heal himself for the full amount while running off on his horse - don't know why this hasn't been mentioned yet, it's extremely annoying... same thing goes for the splurt line of spells, ridiculous. change it when in pvp mode (maybe no heal benefit for tapping mobs while in pvp mode?, can't see why that would be unfair, forcing you to concentrate on pvp when attacked, which should be a natural reaction)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-while in pvp mode, a player can't zone into a safe zone, all other zones allowed of course (i realize this doesn't solve the problem of "zone plugging", maybe have the char come out ld on the other end whenever a player "plugs" and making the ld char defenseless, rendering full pvp awards/penalties for its death. i know some ppl have connection problems, but, heh, you get over it, pvpers are tough&nbsp<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>. "zone hopping" can't be solved this way either, but as long as you fix the problem mentioned above that allows players to actually "heal" themselves by zoning, this could be left untouched.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-faction and mob aggro should be left the same, though i do think the idea of making mobs and assisting mobs&nbsp;concentrate fully on the trainer after 100 feet is an interesting idea. of course this doesn't get rid of rez box training (different issue, with acceptable solution suggestions so far) or fd/fm trains. would make it easier to avoid da trains though, and easier to kill non da trainers. they just might think twice about it</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-fd/fading memories could be changed while in "pvp mode", making the "trainer" (because these skills are mainly used for training) slightly more vulnerable - resist penalty for a short period of time perhaps</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-one shot the one shot skills, heh. make ht/mb/lb (maybe even trueshot, if it's unnerfed), duelist (no flames prz rogies, luv u) a non-existant option for pvp. and don't compensate the sks or necros for it either, they'll learn to adjust, believe me. most sks and necros suck without those options, but only because they rely on them so heavily - they never even considered not using their countless other options which have a lot of power to them as they are, and i can't blame them, i wouldn't either. test test test... and disregard teh whiners for a short while at least</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-channeling: ok this is a very sensitive issue. many high end pure caster classes can channel through basically anything. channeling could be reduced, but if this was done, melee damage would have to be lowered in proportion. that of course would make pure melees weaker in pvp, which shouldn't happen. maybe some number crunching could bring forth a suitable solution. nevertheless, it is a problem, albeit, not the biggest.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-i would say tweak chanter runes, since it's pretty dumb to watch a chanter just rerune himself while being beat on by 6 other players and not lose hp. but consider this option last, after implementing all other changes first. runes are a part of the chanter class, and they do and should depend on them. but like i said, there are some "very high end" issues with this line of spells</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-necros should not get 2 da's, doesn't make any sense, but leave it in the game for all i care. as long as they can't lb/zone to safe zone it's ok with me.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>feel free to add any more effects "pvp mode" should include.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>obviously i've been influenced by ideas from other mmorpgs, but then again, they ripped off a lot from eq, right...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>pvp mode should last for a set amount of time (30 seconds?) after every attack done by a player to the character. consider making ranged melee attacks not count as triggers for pvp mode, the reason for this is there should also be a chance for a player to escape death from someone he can't hit or even see in many cases. balance this issue based on the changes made to the player in "pvp mode".</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>by all means, do NOT reintroduce fear or charm to pvp. it takes away far too much control over your character.</DIV>
<DIV>resists towards snare/root/blind should be left as they are. there's always a very slight chance to get snared, regardless of resists, but only enough to get the adrenaline pumping, not making you afraid of going forth with your pvp tactics. making snare stack with beneficial movement buffs was a very good change btw.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>concerning the pvp reward system. if pvp ever becomes balanced, the amount of "coins" (sz) collected from even con kills could be used to give boni to the individual player when he enters "pvp mode". no bonus should ever be overpowering though.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>the way i see it, the idea of balancing pvp is working towards the utopian vision of giving every player the chance to kill an even con player, based on skill. gear and rare spells should be there to give an edge over someone, but it's important that an experienced pvper can find a way to outsmart the uber "blue" player. and if the uber blue player is also an awesome pk, he should win most fights. the most annoying part of pvp is getting killed and losing xp to someone you know is NOT a good player. but in any case, you learn to deal with it. </DIV>
<DIV>make it fun again. there will always be flame wars in ooc, hehe. but there shouldn't be a reason to quit the game, because of the game itself. and at the moment, in regards to pvp, there just is all the reason to give up, can't' blame anyone that has. i really appreciate the devs taking time to read this. we've waited long enough =). and as you can see, everyone is more than happy to provide you with feedback.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>i'll be monotoring this anxiously and i hope this last effort can bring back the awesome times i used to have on sz. (i realize this is a subjective statement)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-weathered, sz.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
