									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 7687 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_2.gif' border=0 alt='3 ratings - 2.3 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>on tallon zek,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>training is the most useful pvp tactic it seems. druids and wizards with their instant click exodus/nexus gate. paladins/shadowknights can just gather a bunch of mobs up and DA inside a raid. bards can train the whole zone and DA inside a raid or just Fade the mobs unto the raid. warriors can run in with a bunch of mobs and rampage with an OT hammer on the raid causing the warrior to gate and leaving the raid with a huge train.... all too common every day. all of this hinders one guild's progression into the next level up while the guild above them can just mess up their raids and make them wait longer. as it is, the best guild can come train guilds that are flagging or raiding for loot. while the lower guilds dont have access to and are being prevent from gaining access to and disrupting the raids of the better guild or even advancing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>the most notorious pvp'ers on our server have either an insta-kill (harmtouch, lifeburn, manaburn) or they train. the ones with the insta-kill just do any sort of burst dps to get you to the magic 75% mark and boom. what can any non-healing class do against that? run from pvp everytime? these are just lame. if anything the "deathtouch" is the worst of them all because it has no cast time so the person getting hit with it can't heal or run away and it does nothing bad to the shadowknight as the other two drain the health and mana of the caster respectively.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>safety zones are a pain too. i have zoned out and have had people zone out from me many a time leaving the person giving chase a lot of frustration. plane of tranquility seems to be the biggest culprit because most of the pvp is inside the planes expansion anyway. making that zone free to pvp in would probably also cause a lot of headaches as people will be greifed on the way to the plane they are raiding or going to go exp in.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>bards are too overpowered in pvp. straight melees(rogues, monks, warriors, berserkers) have no chance against them because the bard can just run in circles and play songs with selos on the melee while the melee cant do ANYTHING. except use throwing items, which does nothing noticeable.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>bards also need their DA song to take longer to pop. every 3 mins is just ideal for them to zone out, rebuff, get healed up, zone back in and train again. (probably 10 mins like every other class)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>gear is having too much to do with pvp and not skill anymore. each guild is keeping the guild below them down all the time because they outgear them and do not allow them to advance with the ease they are capable of. top guild wears armor with +30 to all resistsfor example, , and going down guilds, lets say each one has +5 to all resists less than the previous. All these guilds include level 65 characters with many AA's but their gear determines how well they will do in pvp. resist checks can't just be modified for high end pvp because while one guild has the very high resists, each guild going down has less and less. this would render their current resists useless as it is nowhere near to par as the best guild on the server. (read: train every single flagging raid from grummus to xegony)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>this leads me to.... each casting class needs at least one lure type spell. not half of their spells. just one or two lure-types. they would do less damage for more mana but have a much less chance of being resisted even by the best-geared. this lure shouldnt be too overpowering but it would give the casters a go-to spell when nothing else will land on their opponent</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>i like the idea of proximety agro listed. where a mob will not agro anyone new a certain distance from his bind spot unless someone else does something to the mobi here or on the other thread.... this would pretty much enfore no training and would keep a person or two from ruining a whole raid. the idea with summoning mobs to summon anyone they agro is quite bothersome as some people lose invis or get agro by accident and need to run away from the mob to a zone out. it would also make pulling on raids impossible as all the pullers would get summoned and die.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>rewards for pvp are not really needed in my opinion. i love to pvp just for the thrill of someone semi-smart on the other side of the computer instead of an npc.fighting&nbsp; only insta-kills take away from that fun. i can see rewards as a useful thing on sullon zek because they LOSE exp when they die so they should GET something when they win... but thats just sullon. rewards are not needed on other pvp servers.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>the problem listed about rallos zek i imagine is a big one too. gear is impossible to attain from another player because every droppable piece of loot they have will be augmented to prevent the looting of it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>resurrection box training has happened a lot on my server too. these boxes need to last a maximum of 20 seconds. there is no need to have them stay up so long at all. most every cleric 50 and up has epic and can just click it again if you missed your rez. (this applies to our server as there seems to be less and less new players to it and everyone seems to be lingering at the high end game). this also applies to translocate boxes which can be used to do the same exact thing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>a crackdown on third-party users would help a lot. i don't so much mind it in pvE but in pvp its just cheating. following, tracking, ghosting, and targetting from anywhere in the zone are all common practices of these people and it bugs the honest people. not much can be done when say a warrior/bard/wizard with a train knows EXACTLY where you are and bring the mobs right into you while escaping unscratched. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>shadowknights need the resist check on their lifetap to be changed so it actually can be resisted because they can just chain-cast it and not even melee to beat almost anyone but another shadowknight with more health who is doing the same thing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>also on a side note, possibly give out an extension of a surname based on amount of player kills a person has acheived. maybe like one at 100, 400, 700, 1000.&nbsp;i guess that can be a reward for the non-sullon zek pvp servers.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>thats all i can think of<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-very-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>with regards,<BR>MMS</DIV>
																		
