			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Class balance is the worst part. SKs are ridiculously overpowered with their super fast casting direct damages and -500 resist check lifetaps mixed in with an unresistable 75% of your HP harmtouch. Pure melee in general are pretty screwed versus many classes. Bards, while not as godly as before their chant line was nerfed, are still super hard to kill and probably are the only class who could take on a well geared, skilled, Shadowknight.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Also, there needs to be a PvP zone or something with events. This would be super fun and be a diversion from the Xp, raiding, or tradeskill day in day out routine most are used to. Raiding and grouping are fun, but fighting another player controlled person(s) is really fun and if EQ offered some form of "game" for PvP I guarantee it would be loved. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>For instance, implement the Plane of War and turn it into a PvP event zone. Put in some creative fun things to do as well as traditional arena's. Make some death match type events. Perhaps bring instancing into it to allow teams to have their own deathmatch tournaments. How about some events with "bots" recruiting NPC's to fight along side you, or even allowing you to command some NPCs. Implement some larger scale stuff to. Some castle sieges or capture the flag type events would rock.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Could allow people to earn some no drop 'toys' through these types of events. Also, perhaps put in some kind of method of tracking your record.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Anyway just spewing some ideas off. I know many people would love some kind of PvP oriented event zone though.</DIV>
																		
