<P>try nuking down a well geared 9k+ warrior/knight with resists above 200 as a none lure caster. insta kill classes have a distorted view of pvp.</P>
<P>the only way players will ever stop ghosting (since it's not possible to fix it technically) is to make it so players don't feel the need to. ideally, every fight should be so close, that you'll want to risk dying for one more second in hope of a killshot and a reward for it.</FONT></P>
<P>many players think it's their RIGHT to win EVERY fight&nbsp;and pvp should be fixed so that they can always win. this is the wrong approach when trying to balance pvp. not a flame, but there's always 2 sides of the story, thanks for posting your's, this is mine... i don't even fight sks anymore, and i'm sure you deal with more ghosters than i do since they know its not worth dying to a 1 button killer. plain and simple facts, not saying it's right, just explaining why it's that way.</FONT></P>
<P>on another note, if there's any way to fix track bug (oh god, who even tracks anymore, lol) and hill bugging, many people would appreciate it.</FONT></P>
