			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<P>the problem with making pok a pvp zone is:</P>
<P>1. it's a great zone for tradeskillers, which it was inteded to be. no more undisturbed tradeskilling with all the traffic bound to go through pok.</P>
<P>2. it's a nice zone for lowbies to get from place to the other, and since sonyeq seems to be interested in making life for newbies a little easier, i'd view this as rather counterproductive</P>
<P>3. faction issues, high lvl npcs. would be a zoo unless npcs were made like the katta bankers... pointless imho</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>in one of my posts i suggested the idea of "pvp mode" and a solution to safe zone hopping if you couldn't zone into a safe zone while in this so called pvp mode. a problem that arises with this, and which is already a big issue is "book camping". only way to somewhat avoid annoying ganking would be to introduce a grace period before entering pvp mode/zone prohibitor when zoning into a pvp zone from a safe zone. but i'm sure there would be ways to exploit this. nevertheless, might be something worth considering.</P>
