			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<P>Ok, here's my little opinion about PvP.</P>
<P>First off, my prime character on my sig is on a blue server, but I do play on RZ also. </P>
<P>What I find annoying about PvP and that should be fixed, is that you get rid of the blocks of non pvp spells. Most of my SK's prime spells that I use in combat are blocked (all my debuffs, taps (except LT), etc). Fear I can do without.....I still remembered when it wasn't nerfed and I could use it...yes Fear is greatly unbalanced in the low-mid game...doesn't work anyway 55+. </P>
<P>What I would suggest to appease the masses that feel that SK's are overpowered, and just don't want to learn proper combat tatics, is that you dampen HT on the PvP servers some more (but then lower the timer....there's a reason it's a 72min timer), or dampen others, but allow us to use our full line of spells....it's part of an SK's battle tatics to use taps and debuffs. </P>
<P>Or am I mistaken and PvP should just be click auto-attack and who ever has the most HP wins?</P>
<P>There's tatics for beating any class no matter their powers....you just need to learn.</P>
<P>That's my 2 cents....feel free to disagree.</P>
