								</span>

								
			
			
									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 7612 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_1.gif' border=0 alt='2 ratings - 1.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<P>Hmmm, well, I am being very optimistic here and hoping it actually gets read, so far the thread has not been ruined.&nbsp; This is from a level 65 magician with 400 AA, who has played most any class in PvP.</P>
<P>- Class imbalances.&nbsp; Unfortunately, this one is a really huge bitch to 'fix' PvP only without messing up PvE.&nbsp; Knights, because of their nature to cast spells in the middle of combat, got slightly nerfed spells that mirror their parent class, but with a 1 second casting time and slow reload.&nbsp; Unfortunately, while that is an absolutely great idea PvE, PvP it makes it so that SK's get better nukes than non-wizards get.&nbsp; Getting a nuke off as a magician with a melee on you is nearly impossible unless you somehow get lucky ghosting up a hill.&nbsp; There is 'no' solution for this problem, unless you were to increase the PvP channeling % somehow magically, for wis/int casters ONLY.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>- Resists.&nbsp; Necromancers are absolutely retarded versus people without high endgear (VT+) but as soon as they reach someone with decent resists they are quite possibly the worst PvP class in game.&nbsp; Why do lifetaps cast in 2.5 seconds, and nukes in 7 seconds?&nbsp; Why do lifetaps always get resisted by soemone with 300+ mr?</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>- Overpowered classes.&nbsp; SK's are the worst offenders.&nbsp; The average 'jousting' round from a plankton greatsword does a ton more damage than a nuke.&nbsp; They have the best PvP lifetap in game.&nbsp; They have the best PvP DoT in game.&nbsp; They have the best non-lure PvP nukes in game.&nbsp; Bards are a different kind of overpowered, being perhaps the only class that can fight 4 or 5 opponents at a time and force them all to zone OOM, dispelled or die.&nbsp; Bards do lack killing power, but their resiliance and their value in group PvP is extreme.&nbsp; Being able to cure crimson potions then rapture people is extremly overpowered.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>- High level resists, however there were excellent posts on the topic by other people.&nbsp; i have some parses available of high level resists, reply and I will be glad to forward them to you.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
																		
										</td></tr>
